ite-Ahead Log (WAL):**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\wal\\WAL.ts` — `WAL` class: append + fsync semantics, UUIDv7 event IDs, monotonic sequence numbers\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\wal\\index.ts` — WAL re-exports\n\n**State management:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\state\\StateManager.ts` — `StateManager`: manages events.jsonl + state.json, optimistic locking, WAL-first ordering\n\n**Recovery and repair:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\recovery\\RecoverySubsystem.ts` — Consistency checking, repair rules, session WAL replay (startup only)\n\n**Session management:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\session\\SessionRegistry.ts` — Full session lifecycle (pending → active → history), project bindings, OpenCode event routing, alias table\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\session\\AgentIdentity.ts` — Agent identity factory functions\n\n**Project management:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\project\\ProjectManager.ts` — Project registration, daemon.json manifest\n\n**Extensions and tools:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\extensions\\ExtensionLoader.ts` — Unified extension loader (plugins, skills, tools, workflows, gates)\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\tools\\ToolDispatcher.ts` — Tool dispatch with permission checks\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\tools\\index.ts` — Tool registration\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\tools\\handlers\\sf-*.ts` — 17 tool handler files (safe-bash, gates, knowledge, doctor, etc.)\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\tools\\lib\\sf_*_core.ts` — 17 core tool implementations\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\extensions\\skill\\SkillLoader.ts`, `SkillRegistry.ts`, `SkillMatcher.ts`\n\n**Other:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\payload-handler.ts`\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\retry\\RetryCounter.ts`\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\cas\\ContentAddressableStorage.ts`\n\n**Tests:**\n- 29 test files in `packages/daemon-core/tests/unit/`, `tests/integration/`, `tests/property/`\n\n### 1.2 Plugin Communication (OpenCode ↔ Daemon)\n\n**Thin Plugin (user-level tools that communicate with daemon):**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\setup\\userlevel-opencode\\tools\\lib\\thin-client.ts` — `DaemonClient` (174 lines): reads `handshake.json`, POSTs to `/api/v1/tool/invoke`, auto-reloads token on 401, singleton pattern. **This is how all `sf_*.ts` tools speak to the daemon.**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\setup\\userlevel-opencode\\tools\\sf_safe_bash.ts` — Example tool using thin client (18 tool files total)\n\n**OpenCode Plugin (sends events to daemon):**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\setup\\userlevel-opencode\\plugins\\sf_specforge.ts` — OpenCode plugin that hooks `tool.execute.before/after`, `event`, `chat.params`, etc. and sends them to the daemon via `ReconnectingDaemonClient`\n\n**Reconnecting Daemon Client:**\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\service-management\\src\\plugin\\reconnecting-daemon-client.ts` — `ReconnectingDaemonClient` (510 lines): HTTP client with exponential backoff, handshake cache invalidation, degraded mode (60s cumulative), health checking, register/getShellEnv\n\n### 1.3 Daemon Startup Management\n\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\opencode-adapter\\src\\integration\\DaemonStartupManager.ts` — `DaemonStartupManager` (610 lines): on-demand daemon startup, process detection, health checking, retry logic\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\plugin-loader\\src\\daemon-init.ts` — `DaemonInit` (603 lines): plugin initialization during daemon startup, dependency ordering, timeout control\n\n### 1.4 CLI Daemon Commands\n\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\cli\\src\\commands\\daemon-client.ts` — CLI commands: `daemon start`, `daemon stop`, `daemon status`, `daemon config`\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\cli\\src\\http\\DaemonClient.ts` — Full-featured HTTP client (826 lines) for CLI-to-daemon communication (axios-based, SSE support, blob handling, retry logic)\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\cli\\src\\distribution\\daemon-healthcheck.ts` — Daemon startup health check: validates schema version against `.installation.json`\n\n### 1.5 Service Management (Daemon lifecycle events)\n\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\service-management\\src\\orchestrator\\healthcheck.ts` — `ServiceHealthChecker`: polls health endpoints, waits for healthy\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\service-management\\src\\orchestrator\\lifecycle-events.ts` — Emits service lifecycle events to daemon via `POST /api/v1/ingest/event`\n\n### 1.6 Observability / Logging\n\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\observability\\src\\event-logger\\index.ts` — `EventLogger` (663 lines): WAL semantics, events.jsonl, fsync, project indices, rebuild state\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\observability\\src\\types\\index.ts` — Event, EventFilter, EventBus, EventLogger interfaces\n\n### 1.7 Configuration / Types\n\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\types\\src\\directory-layout.ts` — `SPEC_DIR_NAME='.specforge'`, `USER_LAYOUT` (log paths, handshake path, lock path), `PersonalPathResolver`, `EnterprisePathResolver`\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\migration\\src\\daemon-startup-integration.ts` — Migration during daemon startup\n\n### 1.8 Additional daemon-related test files\n\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\tests\\e2e\\daemon-wiring.test.ts`\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\tests\\integration\\cli-daemon-integration.test.ts`\n- `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\docs\\plugins\\daemon-integration.md` — Documentation\n\n---\n\n## 2. LOGGING MECHANISM\n\n### 2.1 What Logger Is Used\n\n**There is NO dedicated logging library** (no winston, pino, etc.). The daemon uses **three logging approaches**:\n\n1. **`console.log` / `console.warn` / `console.error`** — Used extensively throughout daemon-core for operational logging. Tagged with prefixes like `[DAEMON]`, `[AUTH]`, `[SSE]`, `[INGEST]`, `[EventBus]`, `[WAL]`, `[SessionRegistry]`, etc. These go to stdout/stderr.\n\n2. **EventLogger** (`@specforge/observability`) — The **structured event persistence layer**. This is NOT a traditional logger — it's a Write-Ahead Log implementation that writes events to `events.jsonl` with fsync for crash safety. Used for all actionable events (state transitions, session lifecycle, tool invocations, permission decisions, etc.).\n\n3. **EventBus with LoggingObservabilityHook** — The EventBus has a built-in `LoggingObservabilityHook` that calls `console.log` on every publish, subscribe, and unsubscribe event. This is instantiated by default in the EventBus constructor.\n\n### 2.2 Where Logs Go\n\n**Path resolution (from `USER_LAYOUT` in `directory-layout.ts`):**\n\n| Location | Path | Content |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Handshake file | `~/.specforge/runtime/handshake.json` | Daemon connection info (port, token, PID) |\n| Daemon lock file | `~/.specforge/runtime/daemon.lock` | PID lock for single-instance enforcement |\n| Daemon state | `~/.specforge/runtime/state.json` | Rebuilt project state checkpoint |\n| Daemon events | `~/.specforge/runtime/events.jsonl` | WAL event log (append-only JSONL) |\n| Service logs | `~/.specforge/logs/` | Service error logs (`specforge-daemon.err`, `opencode-server.err`) |\n| Project runtime | `<project>/.specforge/runtime/state.json`, `events.jsonl` | Per-project state and events |\n\n**Console output** goes to stdout/stderr of the daemon process. In service mode, this is captured by the process manager. In foreground mode, it goes to the terminal.\n\n**Service error logs** are referenced by the health checker at `~/.specforge/logs/specforge-daemon.err` (used in error messages telling users where to look).\n\n### 2.3 Log Levels / Observability Modes\n\nThe observability module defines a **three-tier mode** (`ObservabilityMode`):\n- `'minimal'` — Only critical events\n- `'standard'` — Normal operation events\n- `'deep'` — Detailed debugging events\n\nThe `EventLogger` itself has no log level filtering — it writes ALL events. The mode controls what gets emitted to the EventBus (and thus logged to console via `LoggingObservabilityHook`).\n\nThere are no traditional log levels (DEBUG/INFO/WARN/ERROR) in the console output — it's plain `console.log/warn/error` with tagged prefixes.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW THE DAEMON COMMUNICATES WITH THE OPENCODE PLUGIN\n\nThe communication architecture has **two directions**:\n\n### 3.1 Direction A: OpenCode Plugin → Daemon (Events)\n\nThe plugin (`sf_specforge.ts`) hooks into OpenCode's lifecycle events and sends them to the daemon:\n\n```\nOpenCode Plugin (sf_specforge.ts)\n    ↓ creates ReconnectingDaemonClient\n    ↓ reads ~/.specforge/runtime/handshake.json (port + token)\n    ↓ POST http://127.0.0.1:<port>/api/v1/ingest/register  (one-time)\n    ↓ POST http://127.0.0.1:<port>/api/v1/ingest/event  (per-event)\n    ↓ Authorization: Bearer <token>\n    ↓\nDaemon HTTPServer → handleIngestEvent() → routeIngestEvent()\n    → tool.invoking / tool.invoked / opencode.event / session.compacting / chat.params / chat.headers / shell.env\n```\n\n**Event types sent by the plugin:**\n- `tool.invoking` — Before tool execution (tool name, callID, args)\n- `tool.invoked` — After tool execution (tool name, callID, output)\n- `opencode.event` — OpenCode native events\n- `session.compacting` — Session compaction checkpoints\n- `chat.params` — Chat parameter changes\n- `chat.headers` — Chat header changes (Authorization redacted)\n\n**Reconnection behavior:**\n- `postEvent()` **never throws** — returns `PostResult` with `ok/dropped/reason`\n- Exponential backoff: 1s → 2s → 4s → ... (configurable multiplier)\n- Degraded mode after 60s cumulative backoff\n- Re-reads `handshake.json` on each retry for fresh port/token\n- Token is NEVER logged (security requirement)\n\n### 3.2 Direction B: OpenCode Tools → Daemon (Tool Invocation)\n\nThe 18 `sf_*.ts` tool files use the **thin client** to call daemon tools:\n\n```\nsf_*.ts tool file\n    ↓ import { daemon } from \"./lib/thin-client\"\n    ↓ daemon.invokeTool(\"sf_safe_bash\", args, context)\n    ↓\nthin-client.ts → DaemonClient\n    ↓ reads ~/.specforge/runtime/handshake.json (port + token)\n    ↓ POST http://127.0.0.1:<port>/api/v1/tool/invoke\n    ↓ Authorization: Bearer <token>\n    ↓ Auto-reloads token on 401\n    ↓\nDaemon HTTPServer → handleToolInvoke() → ToolDispatcher.dispatch()\n```\n\n### 3.3 Registration Flow\n\n1. Plugin reads `handshake.json`\n2. Plugin calls `POST /api/v1/ingest/register` with `{ projectPath }`\n3. Daemon creates project context via `ProjectManager.registerProject()`\n4. Daemon creates plugin session via `SessionRegistry.registerPluginSession()`\n5. Response: `{ sessionId, projectId, mode }`\n6. Subsequent events include the `sessionId` for identity\n\n---\n\n## 4. HANDSHAKE / HEALTH CHECK / HOW TO VERIFY DAEMON IS WORKING\n\n### 4.1 Handshake File\n\n**Location:** `~/.specforge/runtime/handshake.json`\n\n**Contents:**\n```json\n{\n  \"schema_version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"pid\": 12345,\n  \"port\": 3847,\n  \"token\": \"<64-char hex string>\",\n  \"startedAt\": 1717000000000,\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"serviceMode\": false\n}\n```\n\n**Lifecycle:**\n1. Daemon generates random 32-byte token at startup via `HandshakeManager.generateToken()`\n2. File is written after HTTP server starts\n3. File permissions: `0o600` (owner read/write only)\n4. Deleted on shutdown via `HandshakeManager.cleanup()`\n\n### 4.2 Single Instance Enforcement\n\n- Lock file: `~/.specforge/runtime/daemon.lock`\n- Uses `flock` on Unix, PID-based locking on Windows\n- Second daemon instance throws: `\"Another Daemon instance is already running\"`\n\n### 4.3 Health Check Endpoints\n\n**`GET /health`** (public, no auth required):\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"status\": \"ok\",\n    \"service\": \"daemon-core\",\n    \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n    \"uptime\": 1234\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**`GET /api/v1/healthz`** (public, no auth required):\n```json\n{\n  \"schema_version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"pid\": 12345,\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"startedAt\": 1717000000000,\n  \"uptimeSec\": 1234,\n  \"activeClients\": 2,\n  \"pendingEvents\": 0,\n  \"lastEventTs\": 1717000005000\n}\n```\n\n**Status values:** `'ok'` | `'degraded'` | `'shutting-down'`\n\n### 4.4 How to Verify Daemon Is Working\n\n**From CLI:**\n```bash\nspecforge daemon status   # Human-readable output\nspecforge daemon status --json  # JSON output\n```\n\n**From code (thin client):**\n```typescript\nimport { daemon } from \"./thin-client\";\n// If the daemon isn't running, this throws:\n// \"Daemon handshake file not found. Is the SpecForge daemon running?\"\n```\n\n**From code (service management):**\n```typescript\nconst checker = new ServiceHealthChecker();\nawait checker.waitForHealthy('specforge-daemon');\n// Throws SVC_HEALTH_CHECK_FAILED if daemon doesn't respond within 5s\n```\n\n**Direct HTTP:**\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:<port>/api/v1/healthz\n```\n\n### 4.5 Startup Health Check\n\nBefore the daemon starts, `DaemonStartupManager` (or the health check hook) validates:\n1. `.installation.json` exists and is parseable\n2. Disk `schema_version` matches code baseline\n3. If code > disk → exit 1 (run migration)\n4. If code < disk → exit 4 (downgrade rejected)\n5. If OK → proceed with startup\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIGURATION FILES THAT CONTROL DAEMON BEHAVIOR\n\n### 5.1 Runtime Configuration (from `DaemonConfig.ts`)\n\n**Environment variables:**\n| Variable | Purpose | Default |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `SPECFORGE_MODE` | `'personal'` or `'enterprise'` | `'personal'` |\n| `SPECFORGE_RUN_MODE` | `'service'` to enable service mode | (not set) |\n| `SPECFORGE_INGEST_ENABLED` | Enable/disable ingest pipeline | `true` |\n\n**CLI arguments (for daemon-core when run directly):**\n| Argument | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `--mode personal\\|enterprise` | Set operation mode |\n| `--foreground` | Run in foreground (default) |\n| `--no-foreground` | Background mode (not fully supported) |\n| `--service` | Service mode |\n\n**Hard-coded defaults in `DaemonConfig.ts`:**\n- `maxPayloadSize`: 64 KiB\n- `schemaVersion`: `'1.0'`\n- `daemonVersion`: `'1.0.0'`\n\n### 5.2 Daemon JSON (`~/.config/opencode/daemon.json`)\n\nThis is the **project manifest** file (referenced by `path-resolver.ts` `resolveDaemonJsonPath()`). It maps project paths to project IDs:\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"projects\": {\n    \"/path/to/project\": { \"projectId\": \"...\", \"registeredAt\": 1717000000000 }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 5.3 Configuration Package (`@specforge/configuration`)\n\nThe plugin reads reconnect parameters from configuration:\n```typescript\nconfig.get('service_management.plugin_reconnect_initial_sec')  // default: 1\nconfig.get('service_management.plugin_reconnect_max_sec')      // default: 60\nconfig.get('service_management.plugin_reconnect_backoff_factor') // default: 2.0\n```\n\n### 5.4 Extension Loader Config\n\n- `extensionsDir`: `'./extensions'` (default)\n- `pluginDir`: `'./plugins'` (default)\n- `grants`: `['filesystem.read', 'env.read']` (default)\n- Per-type enable flags: `skill`, `tool`, `workflow`, `gate`, `plugin` (all `true` by default)\n\n---\n\n## 6. PACKAGES DIRECTORY STRUCTURE (DAEMON-RELATED)\n\n```\npackages/\n├── cli/                          # CLI commands for daemon management\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── commands/daemon-client.ts    # daemon start/stop/status/config\n│       ├── http/DaemonClient.ts         # Full HTTP client (axios, SSE, blob)\n│       └── distribution/daemon-healthcheck.ts  # Schema version check\n├── daemon-core/                  # ★ Main daemon package (77 source files)\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── index.ts                     # Entry point\n│       ├── daemon/Daemon.ts             # Main daemon class\n│       ├── daemon/DaemonConfig.ts       # Configuration\n│       ├── daemon/HandshakeManager.ts   # Handshake & single-instance\n│       ├── daemon/path-resolver.ts      # Path resolution\n│       ├── http/HTTPServer.ts           # HTTP/SSE server\n│       ├── event-bus/EventBus.ts        # Internal pub/sub\n│       ├── state/StateManager.ts        # WAL-first state management\n│       ├── wal/WAL.ts                   # Write-Ahead Log\n│       ├── recovery/RecoverySubsystem.ts # Consistency repair\n│       ├── session/SessionRegistry.ts   # Session lifecycle\n│       ├── project/ProjectManager.ts    # Project registration\n│       ├── extensions/ExtensionLoader.ts # Extension loading\n│       ├── tools/                       # 34 tool files\n│       └── types.ts                     # Core types\n├── configuration/                # Plugin configuration (reconnect params)\n├── migration/                    # daemon-startup-integration.ts\n├── observability/                # EventLogger (logging/WAL)\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── event-logger/index.ts        # EventLogger (663 lines)\n│       └── types/index.ts               # Event, EventFilter interfaces\n├── opencode-adapter/             # DaemonStartupManager (on-demand startup)\n│   └── src/integration/DaemonStartupManager.ts\n├── permission-engine/            # daemon-integration.ts\n├── plugin-loader/                # Plugin initialization on daemon startup\n│   └── src/daemon-init.ts\n├── service-management/           # ReconnectingDaemonClient, health checks\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── plugin/reconnecting-daemon-client.ts\n│       ├── orchestrator/healthcheck.ts\n│       └── orchestrator/lifecycle-events.ts\n└── types/                        # directory-layout.ts (SPEC_DIR_NAME, USER_LAYOUT)\n    └── src/directory-layout.ts\n\nsetup/\n└── userlevel-opencode/\n    ├── tools/lib/thin-client.ts          # Thin HTTP client (all sf_*.ts tools)\n    ├── tools/sf_*.ts                     # 18 tool files using thin client\n    └── plugins/sf_specforge.ts           # OpenCode plugin (hooks → daemon)\n```\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY: Key Architectural Decisions\n\n1. **Single HTTP server** (`HTTPServer.ts`) handles ALL communication: REST API, SSE streaming, tool dispatch, event ingestion\n2. **Bearer token auth** on all endpoints except `/health` and `/api/v1/healthz`\n3. **WAL-first persistence**: `events.jsonl` is fsynced BEFORE `state.json` is updated\n4. **No logging framework** — uses `console.log/warn/error` for operational output and `EventLogger` for structured event persistence\n5. **Handshake file** (`~/.specforge/runtime/handshake.json`) is the sole discovery mechanism — all clients read it to find the daemon's port and auth token\n6. **Single instance enforcement** via file lock at `~/.specforge/runtime/daemon.lock`\n7. **Two operating modes**: `personal` (data stored in project directory) and `enterprise` (data stored in `~/.specforge/projects/<hash>/`)\n\n**Total daemon-related source files: ~77 files in `daemon-core/src/`, plus ~15 files across other packages, plus 18 tool files in `setup/`, plus ~30 test files.**\n</task_result>\n</task>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","sessionId":"ses_18db48c33ffeyi8r2dYHOewJgB","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"deepseek"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore daemon source code","time":{"start":1780034008019,"end":1780034188209}},"id":"prt_e724b5d7700169Fz1hlujdT8Ps","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e724b2f55001wXnizyW4Gy7LZo"},{"reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"baa009c6cac17261f546b84c7af1a68dfc61eb41","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19241,"input":90,"output":340,"reasoning":507,"cache":{"write":0,"read":18304}},"cost":0.000842392,"id":"prt_e724e34fe001MRB8FoFaDUQH