ich is relative to their location. After deployment to `~/.config/opencode/tools/`, the `./lib/thin-client.ts` path still works because the `lib/` directory is also copied alongside the tools.\n\nBut the plugin imports from `../../packages/...` which points OUTSIDE the `setup/userlevel-opencode/` directory. After deployment, this relative path breaks.\n\nSo the question is: was this intentional? Was the plugin SUPPOSED to be loaded from the project directory rather than the user config directory?\n\nLooking at the `opencode.json`:\n```json\n\"plugin\": [\"./plugins/sf_specforge.ts\"]\n```\n\nIf OpenCode resolves `./plugins/sf_specforge.ts` relative to the opencode.json file location (`~/.config/opencode/`), then yes, it would load the broken copy.\n\nBut if there's also a project-level config that overrides this, or if the plugin was designed to be loaded differently...\n\nActually, let me check something: maybe there's supposed to be a symlink instead of a copy. Or maybe there's a `bun link` step. Or maybe the plugin is supposed to be loaded from the project directory via a different mechanism.\n\nLet me check the `bun.lock` file and the specforge manifest for clues.","time":{"start":1780035152082,"end":1780035174871},"id":"prt_e725ce8d2001hwWjgqpVHJYz97","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e725ce226001pczM27AWjvuPpe"},{"type":"text","text":"好问题，让我追踪部署流程，判断这是系统性 bug 还是环境特例。","time":{"start":1780035174876,"end":1780035177163},"id":"prt_e725d41dc001UecFGjFQgUxevl","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e725ce226001pczM27AWjvuPpe"},{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_kxpmLE15w6SEDqTTcWfm8785","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\luo\\.config\\opencode\\specforge-manifest.json"},"output":"<path>C:\\Users\\luo\\.config\\opencode\\specforge-manifest.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"schema_version\": \"1.0\",\n3:   \"shared_version\": \"6.0.0-dev\",\n4:   \"install_