ro","providerID":"deepseek","time":{"created":1780037752538,"completed":1780037765737},"finish":"stop","id":"msg_e728496da001Llllx6Kj9CMsF6","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7"},"parts":[{"snapshot":"d1a73a7037ba591765d37e02113206e2ac4c9f40","type":"step-start","id":"prt_e72849b7f001BKvkcTgSYyGv6n","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e728496da001Llllx6Kj9CMsF6"},{"type":"reasoning","text":"The user wants me to explain what sf_plugin_client.ts does. Let me give a clear, concise explanation based on what I created and its role in the architecture.","time":{"start":1780037754722,"end":1780037755987},"id":"prt_e72849f61001H8GqBtBEzGd2sz","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e728496da001Llllx6Kj9CMsF6"},{"type":"text","text":"`sf_plugin_client.ts` 是 `ReconnectingDaemonClient` 的**独立副本**——把原来分散在 monorepo `packages/` 里的插件客户端代码，合并成**一个零外部依赖的文件**。\n\n### 它解决什么问题\n\n原来 `sf_specforge.ts` 这样导入：\n\n```typescript\n// 原版 — 导入 2 个项目内部模块\nimport { createReconnectingDaemonClient } from \"../../packages/service-management/...\"\nimport { DEFAULT_CONFIG, ... }                   from \"../../packages/configuration/...\"\n```\n\n这两个路径在部署后无法解析（`../../packages/` → `~/packages/` 不存在）。\n\n`sf_plugin_client.ts` 把这两条依赖链的代码全部**内联到单文件**里，只保留 Node.js 内置模块（`fs`、`path`、`os`），部署到 `~/.config/opencode/scripts/lib/` 后就能被插件通过 `../scripts/lib/` 找到。\n\n### 它做什么\n\n就是一个**带自动重连的 HTTP 客户端**，负责插件 ↔ Daemon 之间的通信：\n\n```\nOpenCode 插件 (sf_specforge.ts)\n    │\n    │  import { createReconnectingDaemonClient }\n    │\n    ▼\nsf_plugin_client.ts ──HTTP──▶ Daemon (127.0.0.1:xxxxx)\n    │\n    ├── 读取 ~/.specforge/runtime/handshake.json 获取端口和 token\n    ├── POST /api/v1/ingest/event  发送事件\n    ├── 失败时指数退避重连（1s → 2s → 4s → ...）\n    ├── 超过 60s 累积退避 → 进入降级模式（只打印一次 warning）\n    └── Daemon 重启后自动重读 handshake.json 获取新端口/token\n```\n\n### 类比\n\n就像 `daemon-spawn.ts`（只用 Node 内置模块所以能直接部署），区别是 `sf_plugin_client.ts` 解决的是**通信**问题，而不是**启动**问题。","time":{"start":1780037755990,"end":1780037765097},"id":"prt_e7284a456001TydaNdesOhMVeO","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e728496da001Llllx6Kj9CMsF6"},{"reason":"stop","snapshot":"d1a73a7037ba591765d37e02113206e2ac4c9f40","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":193001,"input":120,"output":463,"reasoning":34,"cache":{"write":0,"read":192384}},"cost":0.001181982,"id":"prt_e7284c92b001lmSkBMY3698SDK","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e728496da001Llllx6Kj9CMsF6"}]},{"info":{"role":"user","time":{"created":1780037944864},"agent":"sf-orchestrator","model":{"providerID":"deepseek","modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro"},"summary":{"diffs":[]},"id":"msg_e7287860a001co02HyVjPbWb7G","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7"},"parts":[{"type":"text","text":"如果以后插件的依赖变化了，这个sf_plugin_client.ts是否要重新生成？如果要重新生成谁来生成？\n为什么不是将plugin的所有依赖拷贝到/scripts/lib/ 中？","id":"prt_e7287860a0029FtYLXSf8k4PWB","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e7287860a001co02HyVjPbWb7G"}]},{"info":{"parentID":"msg_e7287860a001co02HyVjPbWb7G","role":"assistant","mode":"sf-orchestrator","agent":"sf-orchestrator","path":{"cwd":"D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge","root":"D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge"},"cost":0.001904952,"tokens":{"total":194085,"input":626,"output":620,"reasoning":455,"cache":{"write":0,"read":192384}},"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"deepseek","time":{"created":1780037944882,"completed":1780037973543},"finish":"stop","id":"msg_e72878632001QBrWV00U1eJvsM","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7"},"parts":[{"snapshot":"d1a73a7037ba591765d37e02113206e2ac4c9f40","type":"step-start","id":"prt_e72878dde001TaGcGx3ZXnALwO","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e72878632001QBrWV00U1eJvsM"},{"type":"reasoning","text":"The user is asking two important architectural questions:\n\n1. If plugin dependencies change, does sf_plugin_client.ts need to be regenerated? If so, who generates it?\n\n2. Why not just copy all plugin dependencies to /scripts/lib/ instead of creating an inlined copy?\n\nThese are excellent questions. Let me think about them carefully.\n\n**Q1: Regeneration concern**\n\nThe current approach has a fundamental problem: `sf_plugin_client.ts` is a MANUAL COPY of `reconnecting-daemon-client.ts`. If the original changes (bug fixes, new features), this copy won't get updated unless someone remembers to do it. This is a maintenance risk.\n\n**Q2: Why not copy dependencies?**\n\nThe user makes a good point. The alternative would be to copy the actual dependency files (`reconnecting-daemon-client.ts`, `handshake.ts`, etc.) to `~/.config/opencode/scripts/lib/` — similar to how the tools' dependencies are handled. But the problem is that `reconnecting-daemon-client.ts` has its own imports:\n- `import type { HandshakeFile } from \"../types/handshake.js\"` — would need `handshake.ts` too\n- `import { SPEC_DIR_NAME } from \"@specforge/types/directory-layout\"` — this is an npm package import, not a relative path, so it can't be resolved by copying files\n\nSo copying files wouldn't work for the `@specforge/types` import unless we also set up node_modules.\n\nBut wait — we COULD copy all the dependency files AND transform their imports to be self-referential within the scripts/lib/ directory. Essentially a mini-bundling step.\n\nThe better approach might be a build step that automatically generates the bundled file from the source. But that requires a build toolchain.\n\nLet me be honest with the user about the tradeoffs.\n\nFor Q1: Yes, it would need to be regenerated if dependencies change. Currently it's a manual process. The right answer is to add a build script.\n\nFor Q2: We could copy the dependency tree, but there are complications with non-relative imports (like `@specforge/types`). Let me explain the tradeoffs.","time":{"start":1780037948244,"end":1780037958408},"id":"prt_e72879354001GFyQsCLYsIoE9d","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e72878632001QBrWV00U1eJvsM"},{"type":"text","text":"两个问题都很到位。\n\n### Q1：依赖变化后需要重新生成吗？谁来生成？\n\n**是的，需要。** 这是我当前方案的已知缺陷——`sf_plugin_client.ts` 是手动副本，如果上游 `reconnecting-daemon-client.ts` 修了 bug 或加了功能，这里的副本不会自动同步，形成**维护分叉**。\n\n**合理的做法**：加一个构建脚本，自动从源文件生成独立副本。伪代码：\n\n```bash\n# scripts/build-plugin-deps.ts\nbun build packages/service-management/src/plugin/reconnecting-daemon-client.ts \\\n  --outdir setup/userlevel-opencode/scripts/lib/ \\\n  --format esm \\\n  --external 'node:*'          # Node 内置模块不打包\n```\n\n这样每次改上游代码后跑一次构建，`sf_plugin_client.ts` 自动更新，不需要手动维护。\n\n**但**这需要评估 `bun build` 或类似工具在当前项目中的可行性——目前项目没有构建流程专门处理这步。\n\n---\n\n### Q2：为什么不把所有依赖拷贝到 `scripts/lib/` ？\n\n这个直觉是对的——tools 就是这么做的（`~/scripts/lib/`）。但 plugins 的情况有一个关键差异：\n\n**Tools 的依赖是纯文件，Plugins 的依赖跨了 npm 包边界**：\n\n```\nTools 依赖：\n  utils.ts ──import──▶  ../../../scripts/lib/compatibility.ts\n                                   ↑\n                        纯相对路径，拷贝即可\n\nPlugins 依赖：\n  reconnecting-daemon-client.ts\n    ├── ../types/handshake.js          ← 相对路径，可拷贝 ✅\n    └── @specforge/types/directory-layout  ← npm 包名，不可拷贝 ❌\n```\n\n`@specforge/types` 是 npm 包引用——即使把源文件拷贝到 `scripts/lib/`，Bun/Node 解析 `@specforge/types` 时仍然走 `node_modules` 查找链，不会找拷贝过来的文件。\n\n**三种解法对比**：\n\n| 方案 | 做法 | 维护成本 |\n|------|------|---------|\n| **A：内联副本**（当前） | 手动合并为单文件 | 高（需手工同步） |\n| **B：拷贝 + 改写 import** | 拷贝文件并把 `@specforge/types` 改成相对路径 | 中（半自动可行） |\n| **C：构建步骤** | `bun build` 打包为独立文件 | 低（自动化） |\n\n---\n\n### 建议\n\n当前方案 A 是**止血**——先让插件能加载。如果要长期正确，应该在项目里加一个构建脚本（方案 C），把 `sf_plugin_client.ts` 标记为\"生成文件\"（类似 `dist/`），并在部署前自动构建。\n\n要我现在就加上这个构建步骤吗？还是先把当前修改提交，后续单独处理构建？","time":{"start":1780037958410,"end":1780037972904},"id":"prt_e7287bb0a001pHvpLVwizTcPX0","sessionID":"ses_18dbdaef8ffeg8K7ZwQNCwNSn7","messageID":"msg_e72878632001QBrWV00U1eJvsM"},{"reason":"stop","snapshot":"d1a73a7037ba591765d37e02113206e2ac4c9f40","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":194085,"input":626,"output":620,"reasoning":455,"cache":{"write":0,"read":192384}},"cost":0.001904952,"id":"prt_e728